bio.experienceSummary:
Hi parents!
I am an enthusiastic & attentive caretaker with 9 years of experience working with children ages 0-12, and people with special needs ages 5-22. I have experience in roles such as live-in nanny, substitute teacher, babysitter, daycare assistant, special needs aid, camp counselor, housekeeper and more. I have CPR and New York State emergency medical training. 

I am passionate about providing warm, trustworthy services for parents, and working together to help children reach their age appropriate milestones, do active activities daily, connect with nature, develop skills and create a joyful, fun, environment where children feel safe, loved and celebrated. 

I can also provide assistance with cooking, light errands, and homework. Message me for my resume and references.

About me: In my free time, I love spending time in nature, learning about plants, trees, and fungi and hosting events. I enjoy art, Mary Oliver poems, reading, embroidering, building, and people.

description.originalText: Malka took care of our baby boy during the day while we worked from home for 3 months, from the time he was 7 months old until 10 months old. She was very personable and nice to be around in our home. At first our boy was clingy and upset to be left with someone new, but by the end of her time with us he was very excited to see her when she arrived. She read him a lot of books, took him for walks and talked to him a lot, showing him things around the house and neighborhood. She even wrote a nice letter of tips and tricks for the new nanny, which showed how thoughtful she was. She was happy to take instructions and do things the way we ask. She kept us updated on the app that we use and by sending photos during the day. We appreciated having her help and were sad to see her go.

bio.experienceSummary: Hi my name is Bryanna, I'm 20 years old and am currently going to school at Rutgers for Criminal Justice and Psychology. I'm fluent in English and Spanish. I have experience with children ages 6 months to 13 years old. I can prepare meals, change diapers, put kids to bed, and create fun and and engaging activities. I have experience babysitting special needs kids and multiple kids at a time.

Hello! I'm Kerene, a dedicated nanny with over 5 years of experience in childcare and a passion for nurturing young minds. I began my professional journey in 2014, outside of caring for my younger siblings since they were babies, and now they are aged 8, 10, and 13. Alongside my role as a teacher assistant, I've honed my skills in organizing activities, preparing meals, bedtime stories, and even teaching a bit of French. Creating a safe, structured, and loving environment where children can thrive brings me immense joy. I look forward to bringing my experience, positivity, and genuine care to your family!

description.displayText: This review is long overdue! From our first phone call, I knew Kerene was the one. Not only is she punctual, dependable and responsible, but she is so very loving and attentive to our 2 young children. She became family from day 1. My children loved all the fun adventures they went on and always came home with a story. Never a dull moment. I knew my children were in the best care and never had to worry leaving them. She also helped keep the home neat and prepared meals when needed. Kerene is an absolute God sent!

bio.experienceSummary: It's always been my passion to work with children. I started babysitting when I was 14. Throughout high school, I babysat for 3 families both part-time and full-time. At 16, I started working at my community center as a babysitter and assistant teacher. I helped with homework and engaged in creative play. In the fall of 2017, I started attending Seton Hall University and started working for a babysitting agency. I'm still looking for local families to babysit for on an occasional basis (not looking for after school). I have been background checked and fingerprinted, and I'm CPR and First Aid certified.

Need a Reliable Babysitter?
Hello! My name is Isel G., and I'm offering babysitting services for parents who need a break, whether for self-care, a date night, or just some time to recharge. I have over 5 years of professional experience working with children, including 3 years as a head teacher in an infant room and 2 years with the Board of Education. I've also completed college coursework in Early Childhood Education and have experience tutoring children in my community.

As a mother, I understand the importance of providing a safe, nurturing, and enriching environment. I offer flexible babysitting services and would love to help take care of your little ones while you take some time for yourself.

If you're interested, feel free to reach out to me for more details!

description.originalText: We couldn’t be happier with Isel! She are incredibly responsible, patient, and attentive to my children’s needs. My kids absolutely adore her and always looking towards seen her. Isel goes above and beyond, engaging them with creative activities and ensuring they feel safe and cared for. I trust her completely and highly recommend her services to any family in need of a dependable and caring babysitter!

bio.experienceSummary: I have over 20 years of experience working with infants and children! I have a great passion for working with, and caring for them! They play a major part in my life! I have four children, which includes twins, and five grandhildren. Most of my free time is spent with them

description.originalText: I am a FTM. Kathy helped guide me on how to take care of my 4 month old while also caring for him during the summer. She is kind, caring, and knows her stuff! She's knowledgeable and flexible. I enjoyed having Kathy care for my son. I would hire her if I needed child care again.

bio.experienceSummary: I have years of experience caring for children of all ages, from infants to preteens. I am committed to providing a safe, fun, and nurturing environment for the children in my care. I truly enjoy engaging with little ones; I find it rewarding to foster connections with them and be apart of their development. I was a volunteer teacher and babysitter ranging from 2 years old to 12 years old at church for four years. Besides this experience, I was also a caregiver for children of elementary ages, infants, and toddlers for two years. I am also a fluent speaker of Portuguese. I would love to speak with you personally about your family's needs. Please feel free to contact me. Thank you!

I have approximately 6 years of experience with children, from infants to young adults. I just graduated Monmouth University. Prior to college I was involved in many leadership activities such as being captain of my cheer team for 3 consecutive seasons. I was involved in the peer leadership program which mentored elementary, middle, and high school students. Furthermore, I was the cheerleading coach for grades 3-5 in my town.

While in college I worked at a daycare for 2 summers where I was teaching, changing, playing, and helping children as young as 4 months old to Kindergarten. Throughout high school, college, and currently I babysit for multiple families. The children range from 4 months to 10 years old. I am willing to provide references, I have my own car, and am fully vaccinated. I am able to provide a safe, supervised, and caring environment for your little ones!

While in high school I had the pleasure of working at a non profit after school center tutoring, leading dance, and reading classes. During my time there I was promoted to a team leader where I was in charge of managing other teens. I had the opportunity to go on many professional visits and receive extensive one-on-one coaching and support from the directors and coordinators of the center. After graduating high school I began college and working at a charter school in Jersey City where I became an assistant teacher for 1st and 2nd grade. I also had the opportunity to babysit my former high school math teachers children after school hours and on weekends. Last May I was blessed with my baby girl, being a first time mother has been nothing but great. I have many years of experience with children. I am very patient, loving and reliable. Teaching and being around children is a passion of mine and I look forward to all the nanny opportunities that I will have.

I'd describe my personality as bubbly, outgoing, and friendly 

I started working with kids when my nephew & nieces were born in 2012. I have since then taken care of 10 kids & loved being a part of their growth & development. 

One thing you should know about me is I am very punctual & organized. I am great at communication & cooperation. 

My skills include having a strong sense of responsibility, adaptability and being able to create a safe and engaging environment.

I can speak Urdu & Hindi fluently.

description.originalText: My husband & I hired Soha last year to nanny for our 3 children. They're 11,6,and 3 years old. She was outstanding in providing them the proper care. She communicated with us on every move & made us feel at ease. I would have loved to have her for long term!
